{{main|2003 Fed Cup}}
The '''Americas Zone''' was one of three zones of regional competition in the [[2003 Fed Cup]].
==Group I== *Venue: [[Campinas]], [[Brazil]] (outdoor clay) *Date: 23–26 April
The eight teams were divided into two pools of four teams. The teams that finished first in the pools played-off against those that placed second to determine which team would partake in the [[2003 Fed Cup World Group Play-offs|World Group Play-offs]]. The two nations coming last in the pools were relegated to Group II for 2004.
