{{Infobox football club |clubname = FC Obod Tashkent | image = | fullname = Football Club Obod | nickname = | founded = | ground = Obod Stadium | capacity = 4,500 | chairman = | manager = Khayrulla Abdiev | league = First League | season = [[Uzbekistan First League 2017|2017]] | position = 18th ''[[Uzbekistan League]]'' {{decrease}} | pattern_la1=|pattern_b1= |pattern_ra1=_unknown| leftarm1=003C92|body1=003C92|rightarm1=003C92|shorts1=FFFFFF|socks1=FFFFFF pattern_la2=|pattern_b2= |pattern_ra2=| leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=FFFFFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=FFFFFF }}
'''FC Obod Tashkent''' ({{lang-uz|Obod futbol klubi}}) is a [[Uzbekistan]]i [[Football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Tashkent]].
==History== The club was formed in 2012 and started to play in [[Uzbekistan Second League]]. Since 2013 the club played in [[Uzbekistan First League]]. In 2014 ''Obod'' finished third in League. Year later in 2015, the club won First League and promoted to highest tier, [[Uzbek League]] for 2016 season.
