{{Infobox organization |name = Gibraltar Petanque Association |image = Gibraltar Petanque Association logo.jpg |size = 150px |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |map2 = |abbreviation = |motto = |predecessor = |successor = |formation = {{Start date|1999|11|02|df=y}} |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = [[Pétanque]] |headquarters = |location = [[Giralda Gardens]], [[Smith Dorrien Avenue]], [[Gibraltar]] |coords = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> |region_served = |membership = |language = |general = |leader_title = President |leader_name = Mario Victory |leader_title2 = Secretary |leader_name2 = John Dalli |leader_title3 = Treasurer |leader_name3 = Eddie Hammond |leader_title4 = Competition and Media Secretary |leader_name4 = Matthew Edmundson |leader_title5 = Social Secretary |leader_name5 = Pat Edmundson |key_people = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |budget = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |website = {{URL|www.gibraltarpetanque.weebly.com}} |remarks = |former name = }}
The '''Gibraltar Petanque Association (GPA)''' is a small [[pétanque]] federation in the [[British overseas territories|British overseas territory]] of Gibraltar, with the aim of promoting the sport within the territory. The association is made up of approximately 80 members (ranging from ages 13 to 93) with its premises located at the [[Giralda Gardens]] on the [[defensive wall|city walls]] of Gibraltar along [[Smith Dorrien Avenue]]. Its facilities consist of four [[Floodlights (sport)|floodlit]] pistes.<ref name=home>[http://www.gibraltarpetanque.com Official website of The Gibraltar Petanque Association]</ref>
==Competitions== The Federation holds their own competitions regularly. These are as follows:<ref name=home/>
*Men's League *Women League *[[Gibraltar National Day|National Day]] Tournament *Presidents Cup
