{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{Infobox national handball team | Name = Greece | Type = M | Badge = | Badge_size = | Nickname = | Association = [[Hellenic Handball Federation]] | Coach = | Assistant coach = | Captain = | Most caps = | Most goals = | Ranking = | Points = <!-- Home colours --> | pattern_la1 = | pattern_b1 = | pattern_ra1 = | pattern_sh1 = | leftarm1 = 0000DD | body1 = 0000DD | rightarm1 = 0000DD | shorts1 = 0000DD <!-- Away colours --> | pattern_la2 = | pattern_b2 = | pattern_ra2 = | pattern_sh2 = | leftarm2 = FFFFFF | body2 = FFFFFF | rightarm2 = FFFFFF | shorts2 = 000000 <!-- Results --> | Summer Olympics apps = 1 | Summer Olympics first= 2004 | Summer Olympics best = 6th | World cup apps = 1 | World cup first = 2005 | World cup best = 6th | Regional name = | Regional cup apps = | Regional cup first = | Regional cup best = | updated = 29 October 2017 }} The '''Greece national handball team''' is the national [[team handball|handball]] team of [[Greece]] and is controlled by the [[Hellenic Handball Federation]].
Greece has a long tradition in handball. First of all, Greece made it to the handball 2005 World Cup and the 2004 Olympics where they beat Brazil, Korea and won against Egypt in a close game. In the Olympics they lost to eventual champions Croatia, and finished sixth in the tournament. In the World Cup they finished in the sixth position as well.
