{{Unreferenced|date=November 2006}} {{Coord|48|28|44|N|135|02|47|E|region:RU_type:landmark|display=title}} {{Infobox Stadium| | stadium_name = Lenin Stadium | image = Lenin_Stadium,_Khabarovsk_vnutri.JPG |location= [[Khabarovsk]], Russia | opened =1951 |owner= | tenants = [[FC SKA-Khabarovsk]] | seating_capacity = 15,200 }}
'''Lenin Stadium''' ({{lang-ru|Стадион имени Ленина}}) is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Khabarovsk]], [[Russia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[association football]] matches and is the home ground of [[FC SKA-Khabarovsk]]. The stadium holds 15,200 people. It is named after communist revolutionary [[Vladimir Lenin]].
