[[File:Climbing gear - Metolius cams - 01.jpg|thumb|Metolius cams from 1990's.]] [[File:Climbing gear - Metolius Extractor - 01.jpg|thumb|left|Nut Tool - Metolius Extractor]] [[File:Metolius Rock Rings - 01.jpg|thumb|Metolius Rock Rings]] '''Metolius Climbing''' is an American [[rock climbing]] gear manufacturer. Named after the [[Metolius River]] in [[Oregon]], USA, it is headquartered in the city of [[Bend, Oregon]].
The company was started in 1983 by Doug Philips in his garage.<ref name=pdf2010>{{cite web|title=2010 Metolius Climbing|url=http://www.metoliusclimbing.com/pdf/Metolius_2010.pdf|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=OIA>{{cite web|title=Metolius Announces Sales Category Wide Sales Increases - Outdoor Industry Association {{!}} Outdoor Industry Association|url=https://outdoorindustry.org/press-release/metolius-announces-sales-category-wide-sales-increases/|website=Outdoor Industry Association|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref> It got its impetus through a group of committed climbers who came together to push their limits at [[Smith Rock State Park|Smith Rock]] in Oregon's high desert.<ref>http://www.metoliusclimbing.com/about_us.html</ref> Climbing gear available in the 1980s was limited, so they decided to design and build their own equipment, which quickly grew into a business. In 2010 Metolius is employing about 45 people in Bend,<ref name=pdf2010/><ref name=WeighMyRack/> many of them climbers. Company mission statement is “by climbers for climbers”.<ref name=OIA/> In the last decade, some of the production like manufacturing of carabiners were moved overseas.<ref name=WeighMyRack>{{cite web|last1=Dennis|first1=Alison|title=11 Things I Learned From Touring the Metolius Headquarters {{!}} WeighMyRack Blog|url=http://blog.weighmyrack.com/11-things-i-learned-touring-metolius/|website=WeighMyRack Blog|accessdate=5 December 2016|date=18 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Frye|first1=Karissa|title=Buy Responsibly: American Made Climbing Gear|date=August 24, 2016|url=http://www.climbing.com/gear/buy-responsibly-american-made-climbing-gear/|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref>
== Present day == Metoilus is one of the leading manufacturers of climbing gear, including rock climbing, big wall and bouldering gear.<ref name=OIA/><ref>{{cite web|title=Nuts and Cams Climbing Gear Reviews by Rock & Ice Magazine|url=http://www.rockandice.com/nuts-and-cams-reviews|website=www.rockandice.com|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref> In 2016 it was manufacturing wide range of climbing equipment, including: [[spring-loaded camming device]]s, climbing nuts and hexcentrics, [[belay device]]s, [[portaledge]]s, [[Climbing harness|harness]]es, [[carabiner]]s, slings, helmets, haul bags, crash pads, and artificial climbing holds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Metoilus Product Manuals|url=http://www.metoliusclimbing.com/instruction-manuals.html|accessdate=5 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Don’t Call It a Comeback {{!}} Climbing Business Journal|url=http://www.climbingbusinessjournal.com/dont-call-it-a-comeback/|website=www.climbingbusinessjournal.com}}</ref>
